Entire options are listed here

RE2C --input {fileroot}			Specify input file
     --output {fileroot}		Specify output file	
     --cor {fileroot} 			Specify correlation matrix file
     --threads N			Specify number of threads that will be used in this analysis

Input File Format:  
	1. Each rows represent a SNPs. 
	2. The first column of each rows is for rsID, and the following columns are pairs of effect size and its standard error of Nth study.

Example command
bash RE2C.sh --i ./example/example_input.txt --o ./out --c ./example/example_cor.txt
 
Please visit the RE2C website for more details
